12/01/2004
JERUSALEM, Israel -- Macedonian Foreign Minister Ilinka Mitreva is wrapping up a three-day visit to Israel on Monday (12 January). 
During talks with counterpart Silvan Shalom, Mitreva discussed possibilities for boosting economic co-operation, as well as the preparation of bilateral agreements on protecting investments and avoiding double taxation. 
The two ministers also agreed on liberalising the visa regime. 
This marks the first visit by a foreign minister of Macedonia since the establishment of diplomatic relations between the two countries in December 1995. 
(MIA - 11/04/01)
